<h2 class="bold font-l">Nisekoi</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Kosaki and Chitoge can't make a poker face to save their lives. </p>
<p class='example_row'>Example of:<br><a href="/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoPokerFace" class='trope-example-link'>No Poker Face</a></p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="7mzqzh" data-video-descrip="Chitoge Kirisaki apologizes to Raku Ichijou for her earlier behavior towards him, but in English so he won't understand. Said English is clear, properly pronounced, and has only the faintest trace of a Japanese accent." data-video-title="Nisekoi - Chitoge's English Apology (ep. 6)" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/7mzqzh_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/7mzqzh.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/SurprisinglyGoodEnglish" data-video-tropename="Surprisingly Good English" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Manga/Nisekoi" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/7mzqzh.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Nisekoi - Chito...</span></p>
</a>
